        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 13 at 2:12PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 212 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southwest of Lordsburg, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lordsburg, Steins, Cotton City, Road Forks, Lordsburg Playa, Granite
Gap, Shakespeare, and Pyramid Mountains.

This includes Interstate 10 in New Mexico between mile markers 1 and
31.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
